If the optic nerve (II) or olfactory tract is interrupted, will it regenerate? <image 1> 

A. No, will not regenerate.
B. Yes, will regenerate.

The optic nerve (cranial nerve II) and the olfactory tract do not have the ability to regenerate after being interrupted or severed. This is due to the fact that these structures are composed of axons from neurons in the central nervous system (CNS), which generally lack the capacity for regeneration following injury.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

A. No, will not regenerate.
